                    "description": "Company Profile\n\nDUTCH FEATURES GLOBAL ENTERTAINMENT.\n\nDutch Features represents Leading European producers and is headed by industry veteran, Pim van Collem. The company\u2019s focus is to market and license selected, high -concept European and Dutch language feature films, prime-time Drama series and Event mini-series to international distributors and International Networks and new media platforms.  \n\nFor more then three decades, Van Collem has been successful in the International licensing of feature films and Drama-series, both domestically and internationally and across all platforms; theatrical, home entertainment and television. \n\n\nVan Collem, former president of Endemol International Distribution and Polygram Filmed Entertainment Benelux, is a renowned distribution professional who is best known for marketing and selling thriving US network miniseries which were licensed  to European Broadcasters; successful titles such as the ABC networks Event Mini-series: \"Joan Of Arc\", starring: Jacqueline Bisset, Peter O\u2019Toole and Shirley Maclaine and the TNT networks production successful miniseries:The Audrey Hepburn story, starring Jennifer Love Hewitt. \nIn addition; Van Collem was also the architect behind the output-deal with Arnon Milchan\u2019s renowned film and television Production Company; New Regency Enterprises, which supplied the firm with top-quality studio films, such as : \u201cHeat\u201d and \u201cJFK, and \u201cThe Devils Advocate\u201d. and became the foundation for the first historic first non studio output deal with the Dutch Public Broadcasters (NPO)",
                    "title": "CEO & President",
